	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=12296&amp;mid=110385428443279">They all drop hairs</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=12296&amp;mid=110385428443279#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Thu, Dec 23rd 9:11 PM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=183097"><span id=" ">Grigner</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">49 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Default [1.89]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>I spent 4 hours in CS and got 8 hairs. I got 5 from enticers, 2 from enchantresses and 1 from a seductress. I didnt bother using the mezz and mana drain strategy. I made a pet and buffed it with NDT and haste. I pulled a siren with psychosis and let pet finish it off while I nuked some more. Not once did they charm my pet. No need to mana drain since nothing stuck on me.<br/><br/>I killed the sirens at the SS tower and SG entrance. There is also another spot in the middle of the bay, where sirens spawn, just north of the halfway point between the sirens near the SS tower and the sirens near the SG entrance. There is a rock on the bottom of the ocean where 4 sirens will spawn. The rock is west of the large shipwreck in the middle of the bay. There is also 1 that spawned by itself east and slightly north of the rock<br/><br/>If you start at the SG entrance and work your way down to the SS tower area you can go back to SG entrance before the sirens there respawn. Depending on how fast you kill them of course.<br/><br/><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Dec 23 21:19:12 2004</em></p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />Mentalius Mindripper<br/>Level 70 Enchanter<br/>Riders of the Apocalypse<br/>Lanys T'Vyl<br/><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1141495 target=akztarg>My Stuff</a></td></tr>
