	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=278938"><span id=" ">ryunotao</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">117 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Decent [2.81]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Okay, I've tried this at a couple levels, and it's only now really effective at 56.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you have higher MR than me (mine's crap), then you could probably do this sooner.  Anyway, the point where three spawn together near the skyshrine zone... just use harmony of nature on two, and put swarm of pain and drones of doom on the one you want to pull.<br/><br/>Now run back to the skyshrine ramp and sit on the first platform, facing towards the siren.  She'll have a hard time with the pathing and struggle up the hill.  She probably won't get within casting distance of you until your dots wear off;  at this point snare her, and put the dots right back on.  this way if you get mezzed, she's still getting damaged. keep yourself with levitate, because if she fears you and you go nuts around here without lev... could be a disaster.<br/><br/>oh yeah, almost forgot to mention that i got mine off a siren enticer who was green to me (i clarify because once in a while there was a lt blue one).<br/><br/><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Aug  3 11:37:26 2004</em></p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
