	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=12296&amp;mid=10483199906875">RE: siren strategy</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=12296&amp;mid=10483199906875#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Sat, Mar 22nd 3:34 AM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=85336"><span id=" ">bretappleby</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">38 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Decent [3.30]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>I have been soloing these (as a bard) from level 53 but you may be able to earlier.&nbsp;&nbsp;I have tried fighting underwater but I found the lack in manoeuvrability and the sharks adding a liability.  I have been pulling to the Sirens Grotto zone, fairly easy to single-pull just by slowly going down the tunnel and waiting for proximity agro.  The agro from a long way and the first you will know is when spells hit you(or hopefully you resist them).<br/><br/>I always (unless I was mezzing them) played Psalm of Mystic shielding (Magic Resist) and I did work on getting my MR up with equipment to about 90 before singing.  Previously when I tried it was the nukes that hurt.  Once the agrod me I slowly backed up to land until they left the water - there I mezzed them (healed if necessary) and de-buffed to get rid of runes and damage shields.  From there I straight meeleed (fear kiting took too long) and mez healed if necessary.  Most times I didn't need to mez heal as I could melee the dark blues 50% of the time in one go.<br/><br/>Sometimes  2 came at once - 3 options 1.  Charm one to kill the other then zone 2. Charm one to kill other then melee ex-pet 3.  Zone and try again.  All 3 worked for me.<br/><br/>4 Deaths before trying this tactic, none since, have failed on one combine, and now I'm ready for the next one, wish me luck.<br/></p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
